<p class="article-lead">A pre-production perfume sample is the first opportunity to approve the complete product: liquid, fill, closure, decoration, label, carton and assembly together.</p><h2>What to check</h2><p>Confirm scent reference, appearance, fill, spray, leakage, cap fit, decoration position, artwork content, batch-code area and box protection. Compare physical colors and finishes with approved references. Verify that the scent name matches every printed component.</p><p>Record any difference between the sample and intended mass production, such as hand-applied decoration or substitute material. Approve with a dated sample code and photographs, but retain the physical unit when possible. A fragrance evaluation vial is not a substitute because it cannot prove package function.</p>
